<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-07T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="137" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6374/1071: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-07T12:00:00-04:00">January 7,
                                1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>7. I believe the Chilean Government has a definite plan for procedure in
                            the liquidation of Cosach but it has made no official statement and has
                            refused to give any intimation to the company concerning it. It is of
                            immediate importance to American interests to know what changes in the
                            capital structure are contemplated. I suggest that, unless the
                            Department perceives some objection, I talk with the Minister of
                            Finance.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>